  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1 300\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dab \u0dab\u0dba\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dc0\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "300 million given to Vee has been offset against an old loan",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A spokesperson of the Ministry of Agriculture said that due to the retention of an amount of 300 million rupees that the Rice Marketing Board had credited to a state bank for the purchase of rice from the farmers, the payment to the farmers who had been given rice was in crisis.",
        "The spokesperson also mentioned that the Wheat Marketing Board has withheld this amount to pay a loan premium to the concerned state bank.",
        "The Agriculture Ministry spokesman said that the relevant loan installment is due on the ninth of September and by withholding money before that, the farmers have not been able to pay the money for paddy.",
        "The government has agreed to provide money for the purchase of paddy from the farmers, and until the money is received, the amount of 300 million rupees held by the Paddy Marketing Board has been deposited in a government bank to make related payments to the farmers.",
        "The spokesman of the Ministry of Agriculture said that the rice marketing board had set a guaranteed price and proceeded with the purchase in order to stop the robbery and purchase from the farmers."
      ],
